h4. Main Sympton 
Read from/write to the primary node always result in extra delay due to network error below, if the invocations are longer than $(10seconds+heartbeatFrequencyMS) apart. If `heartbeatFrequencyMS = 2000`, invocation interval cannot be longer than 12 seconds, or there will be extra delay on read/write. If `heartbeatFrequencyMS = 5000`, invocation interval cannot be longer than 15 seconds, so on and so forth. The following log entries are generated when the delay happens.

