h3. What problem are you facing?

I am attempting to connect to a mongo replicaset with the node.js driver, however, I am using a proxying service in between ([https://github.com/coinbase/mongobetween|https://github.com/coinbase/mongobetween).] [).|https://github.com/coinbase/mongobetween).] When I connect my node app to the proxy, mongo will return this error:
{code:java}
MongoServerSelectionError: The client metadata document may only be sent in the first isMaster{code}
The driver for node.js will then continue to retry until it times out.

I believe the issue is a result of the driver for node.js [_always_ sending client metadata with the initial handshake|https://github.com/mongodb/node-mongodb-native/blob/v4.2.0/src/cmap/connect.ts#L205], even during a retry when the original error was a result of the client metadata in the first place. If I remove the client property from the handshake document, everything works just fine.
{code:java}
delete handshakeDoc.client;
{code}
 

I tested this same scenario with the MongoDB shell and the Python driver, and both of those work. Only the node.js driver seems to have this issue.
h3. What driver and relevant dependency versions are you using?

[4.2.0|https://github.com/mongodb/node-mongodb-native/releases/tag/v4.2.0]

 

